                / %h2 Research : Information Sheet And Consent Form
                / %br/
                %h2 
                  %b Research
                
                %p
                  B-Change Foundation is currently undertaking a research project to better understand how users use and engage with
                  = succeed "." do
                    %b PLUS 

                %p  The study is being conducted by researchers who are interested in exploring the role of technology in community development programs. The results of the study will be shared with PLUS users.

                %p  By ticking ‘I agree’ below:
                %ul{:style=>"list-style:circle;font-size: 15px;color: #000000;"}
                  %li You give permission for these researchers to collect information about you from 
                  = succeed "." do
                    %b PLUS 
                  All information collected will be de-identified (ie. made anonymous).The results of the study may be published by one of these researchers in a form that will not identify you in any way.
                  %li
                    You can withdraw your participation from this research project at any time, without consequence, and without giving a reason(you can do this by changing the settings in your profile).

                
                %p
                  If you have any concerns about the research please contact him at
                  %u
                    %a{href: "mailto:Benjamin.J.Hanckel@student.uts.edu.au"} Benjamin Hanckel
                  or his supervisor Associate Professor
                  = succeed "." do
                    %u
                      %a{href: "mailto:alan.morris@uts.edu.au"} Alan Morris
                  If you would like to talk with someone not connected with the research you may contact the 
                  %u
                    %a{href: "mailto:Research.ethics@uts.edu.au"} Research Ethics Officer
                  at the University of Technology, Sydney, Australia.
                %span.class-agree
                  = radio_button_tag 'user[accept_terms]',"true",true, :class=>"radio_class"
                  Yes, I Agree
                  = radio_button_tag 'user[accept_terms]',"false",false, :class=>"radio_class"
                  I do not agree
